attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Intel 80386, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a Linux IoT botnet, likely a variant of Gafgyt (Bashlite) or Mirai, designed for DDoS attacks and persistent presence. Key malicious behaviors include: 1) Daemonization and masquerading by forking, setsid, and using prctl to rename itself to 'systemd' or common service names (telnetd, udhcpc, etc.) to evade detection. 2) Competitive 'killer' functionality in functions sub_8050b00 and sub_8053e70, which scan /proc and /proc/net/tcp to identify and kill other processes occupying specific ports or having certain characteristics. 3) Anti-reboot mechanisms by opening /dev/watchdog to prevent system resets. 4) Implementation of multiple DDoS attack vectors (TCP/UDP/SYN floods) seen in functions like sub_804e2f0 and sub_804c6f0, which involve raw socket manipulation and manual packet header construction.
